1
00:00:12,120 --> 00:00:13,370
Damn it!

2
00:00:13,410 --> 00:00:14,450
I'm screwed!

3
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:33,930
Wait!

4
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:39,270
Thanks.

5
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:49,150
Hey!

6
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,030
Sit here.

7
00:00:53,580 --> 00:00:54,620
Right here.

8
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:00,750
Hey!

9
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:02,420
Your legs are like jelly.

10
00:01:02,540 --> 00:01:03,000
What?

11
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:04,750
No wonder your control is terrible.

12
00:01:07,210 --> 00:01:07,630
Piss off!

13
00:01:07,670 --> 00:01:09,090
I don't need a manager.

14
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:11,050
Your balance is terrible.

15
00:01:16,810 --> 00:01:17,140
Haha.

16
00:01:17,930 --> 00:01:18,680
Haha!

17
00:01:37,830 --> 00:01:38,620
What the hell!

18
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:43,750
Are you a ghost?

19
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:46,460
You always appear out of nowhere!

20
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:51,630
Let go of me.

21
00:01:51,930 --> 00:01:52,760
No,

22
00:01:55,550 --> 00:01:57,510
you need to eat real food.

23
00:01:58,470 --> 00:01:59,430
Yeah, so let me eat.

24
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:01,020
This is my first meal today.

25
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:02,520
You're an athlete.

26
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:03,940
You can't just live on carbohydrates.

27
00:02:03,980 --> 00:02:06,610
Don't you know
how important diet is?

28
00:02:06,650 --> 00:02:07,900
What does what I eat

29
00:02:07,940 --> 00:02:10,070
have to do with throwing strikes?

30
00:02:10,110 --> 00:02:10,690
Stop.

31
00:02:10,740 --> 00:02:12,900
If you want to throw strikes, eat properly.

32
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:25,580
You made these?

33
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:26,880
Of course.

34
00:02:27,210 --> 00:02:29,090
This is the first basic skill for a manager.

35
00:02:29,550 --> 00:02:31,630
Don't say that.

36
00:02:31,670 --> 00:02:33,340
I'm just a student athlete.

37
00:02:34,010 --> 00:02:34,890
Just eat.

38
00:02:35,390 --> 00:02:37,140
If I eat this, you become my manager.

39
00:02:37,180 --> 00:02:38,010
Really?

40
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:39,470
That's what you'd say.

41
00:02:39,510 --> 00:02:40,680
You got me!

42
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:42,640
No, thanks.

43
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:43,640
Eat it.

44
00:02:43,690 --> 00:02:45,020
Don't leave a single bite.

45
00:02:46,730 --> 00:02:48,070
No strings attached, right?

46
00:02:48,110 --> 00:02:48,690
None.

47
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:49,780
Really?
Really.

48
00:02:50,230 --> 00:02:51,690
I'm just doing my duty as a fan.

49
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:56,490
I'm not interested in that kind of stuff.

50
00:02:56,530 --> 00:02:57,780
Wipe your drool.

51
00:03:00,740 --> 00:03:01,580
Thanks.

52
00:03:01,830 --> 00:03:03,080
Batting second, first baseman Kang Tae-sung.

53
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:03,710
Here.

54
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,210
Batting third, third baseman Park Ji-yoon.

55
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:05,710
Here.

56
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,290
Batting fourth, catcher Kim Jeong-ho.

57
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:07,830
Here.

58
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:10,000
Batting fifth, designated hitter Yoo Chang-soo.

59
00:03:10,130 --> 00:03:10,500
Here.

60
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,260
Batting sixth, shortstop Choi Ha-seong.

61
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:12,800
Here.

62
00:03:13,630 --> 00:03:15,130
Batting seventh, center fielder Lee Mun-ho.

63
00:03:15,180 --> 00:03:15,590
Here.

64
00:03:16,550 --> 00:03:18,470
Why am I not on the list?

65
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:19,390
You?

66
00:03:19,850 --> 00:03:20,890
You're useless.

67
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,060
If the game goes long,

68
00:03:25,230 --> 00:03:26,600
I might be useful.

69
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:28,560
And if I keep practicing,

70
00:03:28,610 --> 00:03:30,360
maybe I'll eventually throw strikes.

71
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:32,820
How many years has it been?

72
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:35,950
Don't hold onto unrealistic hopes.

73
00:03:36,180 --> 00:03:38,300
Stop wasting time, got it?

74
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,740
You're not on the list
until you pass the tryout.

75
00:03:42,120 --> 00:03:43,790
Not happy, then leave.

76
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:54,510
Okay. Next.

77
00:04:02,510 --> 00:04:03,600
Bullpen's done,

78
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:05,640
head to the field for batting practice.

79
00:04:09,690 --> 00:04:10,650
What are you doing?

80
00:04:11,060 --> 00:04:11,690
You're not going?

81
00:04:11,730 --> 00:04:13,530
Why would I do batting practice?

82
00:04:13,570 --> 00:04:15,610
Just pitch for practice.

83
00:04:15,690 --> 00:04:17,570
No.

84
00:04:17,610 --> 00:04:20,120
Be grateful you're
not completely excluded.

85
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:21,490
Geez.

86
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:29,120
Not excluded?

87
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:30,420
I'm a discard.

88
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:42,220
You can't stay here during practice.

89
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:44,640
What?

90
00:04:44,810 --> 00:04:45,810
Why? Because of Jeong-ho?

91
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:47,020
He didn't say anything.
Really?

92
00:04:49,060 --> 00:04:49,940
That's weird.

93
00:04:50,150 --> 00:04:50,850
Hey.
Throw one.

94
00:04:52,310 --> 00:04:53,230
I'll catch.

95
00:04:53,980 --> 00:04:54,730
No.

96
00:04:55,110 --> 00:04:55,860
Why?

97
00:04:56,690 --> 00:04:57,530
I might hit you.

98
00:04:59,530 --> 00:05:00,360
What?

99
00:05:00,820 --> 00:05:02,320
You're worried about me?

100
00:05:02,700 --> 00:05:04,910
No, I just don't wanna hurt you.

101
00:05:05,990 --> 00:05:07,580
But you know what?

102
00:05:08,290 --> 00:05:10,500
Your ball can't hurt me.

103
00:05:13,170 --> 00:05:14,630
Wanna bet?

104
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,510
What?

105
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:21,640
Scared?

106
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:24,010
I won't say it twice.

107
00:05:24,050 --> 00:05:25,640
What if it's more than just a hobby to me?

108
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:26,260
Will you do it?
You used to be a player?

109
00:05:27,140 --> 00:05:28,230
Of course.

110
00:05:28,270 --> 00:05:29,140
Long time ago.

111
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:30,810
Yeah, I used to be pretty good.

112
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:32,060
But you don't play now?

113
00:05:33,230 --> 00:05:35,820
I prefer watching others play now.

114
00:05:36,550 --> 00:05:37,060
Alright,

115
00:05:37,530 --> 00:05:38,320
let's make a bet.

116
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,780
But wear protective gear.

117
00:05:40,820 --> 00:05:41,660
Okay, deal.

118
00:05:41,950 --> 00:05:42,670
What's the bet?

119
00:05:43,030 --> 00:05:43,950
Well,

120
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:46,700
if I catch every single one of your pitches,

121
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:49,000
you let me be your manager.

122
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:49,580
What do you think?
If you can't catch them?

123
00:05:50,710 --> 00:05:52,960
Then it's like we never met.

124
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:53,670
Huh?

125
00:05:54,210 --> 00:05:54,750
I mean

126
00:05:54,790 --> 00:05:56,420
I'll disappear from your sight.

127
00:05:58,260 --> 00:05:58,960
Fine.

128
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:02,180
Show me everything you've got.

129
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,550
Slider.

130
00:06:03,590 --> 00:06:05,550
It breaks more than you think.

131
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,850
Nice.

132
00:06:18,230 --> 00:06:18,900
Changeup.

133
00:06:18,940 --> 00:06:20,860
It goes straight then drops.

134
00:06:25,990 --> 00:06:26,580
Next.

135
00:06:29,870 --> 00:06:31,500
Curveball. Big drop.

136
00:06:36,330 --> 00:06:37,540
Last one is a fastball?

137
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:43,630
If you catch this one, you win.

138
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:50,270
If you catch this one, you win.

139
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:11,750
Hey.

140
00:07:11,790 --> 00:07:14,080
That must be 160km/h.

141
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,250
You're exaggerating.

142
00:07:15,750 --> 00:07:16,420
Not, I'm not.

143
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:18,080
Even if it was a strike right down the middle,

144
00:07:18,130 --> 00:07:19,500
catching that would be tough.

145
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:20,710
So what? It was a ball.

146
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:21,050
Come on.

147
00:07:21,550 --> 00:07:23,050
You can throw strikes.

148
00:07:24,170 --> 00:07:24,840
Throw it.

149
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:28,760
No, it's over.

150
00:07:30,510 --> 00:07:31,140
What?

151
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:32,350
What do you mean?

152
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:35,440
You won.

153
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,810
But I didn't catch it.

154
00:07:36,850 --> 00:07:38,810
I threw a pitch you couldn't catch.

155
00:07:39,310 --> 00:07:39,900
What?

156
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:41,270
Changed your mind?

157
00:07:41,690 --> 00:07:42,650
Don't want me as your manager?

158
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:43,820
No.

159
00:07:43,990 --> 00:07:45,450
I'll do it, I'll be your manager.

160
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:49,570
Let's make it official.

161
00:07:49,620 --> 00:07:51,160
No quitting midway.

162
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,620
Of course not.

163
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:01,090
Thank you, Manager.

164
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,170
Thank you.

165
00:08:12,350 --> 00:08:13,430
All of this is just for you?

166
00:08:14,390 --> 00:08:15,310
This is enough for four people.

167
00:08:16,350 --> 00:08:17,770
Seems normal for a guy.

168
00:08:17,810 --> 00:08:18,810
Enjoy.

169
00:08:18,850 --> 00:08:19,690
Thank you.

170
00:08:20,610 --> 00:08:21,360
Looks delicious.

171
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:22,230
I'll start.

172
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:25,530
Wait,

173
00:08:25,570 --> 00:08:27,110
you said no flour.

174
00:08:27,150 --> 00:08:28,280
You kept nagging me about it,

175
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:29,990
and now you don't care?

176
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:30,820
It's rice flour.

177
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:31,570
What?

178
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:33,370
Korean five-grain rice.

179
00:08:33,410 --> 00:08:34,830
I checked the ingredients.

180
00:08:36,450 --> 00:08:37,040
Really?

181
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:39,870
I have a question.

182
00:08:40,130 --> 00:08:40,500
What?

183
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:41,670
Go ahead.

184
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:43,800
Did you go easy on me?

185
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:45,630
You mean the last ball?

186
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:47,630
It barely left your hand.

187
00:08:48,090 --> 00:08:48,720
You know me.

188
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:50,300
I can't throw strikes.

189
00:08:50,510 --> 00:08:52,010
Yeah, that's when there's a batter.

190
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:53,640
Why would I do that?

191
00:08:53,850 --> 00:08:54,640
So I'm asking you.
Why did you do that?

192
00:08:55,390 --> 00:08:56,680
My shoulder

193
00:08:57,060 --> 00:08:58,230
was a bit tight then.

194
00:08:58,270 --> 00:08:59,890
Your story keeps changing.
Sounds like an excuse.

195
00:08:59,940 --> 00:09:01,270
Whatever you say.

196
00:09:01,310 --> 00:09:02,610
Fine, whatever I say.

197
00:09:02,770 --> 00:09:03,440
Anyway.

198
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,940
You're the manager now.

199
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:05,730
Got any plans?

200
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:06,900
Plans?

201
00:09:07,780 --> 00:09:08,820
It's all in here.

202
00:09:08,860 --> 00:09:09,400
Really?

203
00:09:12,370 --> 00:09:12,820
What's this?

204
00:09:25,550 --> 00:09:26,710
You're totally obsessed.

205
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:30,050
Throw strikes in games.

206
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:32,300
Pick up trash.

207
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:34,300
Eat three bowls of food for breakfast.

208
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:35,470
Three bowls?

209
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:39,060
What does that have to do with throwing strikes?

210
00:09:40,310 --> 00:09:42,060
See that little disclaimer?

211
00:09:42,100 --> 00:09:42,690
Read it.
At the bottom?

212
00:09:43,610 --> 00:09:44,650
Yeah, quiet small.

213
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:46,230
No complaints?

214
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:47,730
Yeah. No complaints.

215
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:48,610
What the...

216
00:10:15,510 --> 00:10:16,260
What?

217
00:10:23,310 --> 00:10:24,230
What do you want?

218
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:25,060
Let's go.

219
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:27,900
This is way earlier than we agreed.

220
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,530
I changed my mind.

221
00:10:29,690 --> 00:10:31,030
I haven't had breakfast yet.

222
00:10:31,070 --> 00:10:32,700
You said I need to eat breakfast.

223
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,030
Check this out.

224
00:10:34,660 --> 00:10:35,070
Gosh,

225
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,660
you're totally obsessed.

226
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:39,370
Starting today, you run 10 kilometers every day.

227
00:10:39,740 --> 00:10:40,700
Ten kilometers?

228
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:41,790
Yeah.

229
00:10:42,460 --> 00:10:44,290
For stable control,

230
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:46,380
a strong lower body is the number one priority.

231
00:10:47,710 --> 00:10:49,500
I'm training.

232
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:50,670
What did I say?

233
00:10:51,670 --> 00:10:53,130
Strong lower body?

234
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,720
No complaint.

235
00:10:54,970 --> 00:10:55,300
Damn.

236
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:57,010
No complaint.

237
00:10:57,470 --> 00:10:58,760
Ten K is too much.

238
00:10:58,810 --> 00:11:00,220
If you don't leave now, you'll be late.

239
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:00,810
Got it?

240
00:11:02,310 --> 00:11:03,060
Let's go,
hurry.

241
00:11:04,100 --> 00:11:05,400
Okay, coming.

242
00:11:06,060 --> 00:11:07,110
Wait for me.

243
00:11:18,390 --> 00:11:19,430
Good.

244
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:25,960
Nice.

245
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:30,300
Nice.

246
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:31,380
Tae-hui.
Yeah?

247
00:11:33,010 --> 00:11:34,670
Isn't 10K too much?

248
00:11:35,470 --> 00:11:36,050
Ten K?

249
00:11:36,550 --> 00:11:38,050
You're already halfway done.

250
00:11:38,090 --> 00:11:39,760
Easy for you to say on your bike.

251
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:40,720
Are you tired?

252
00:11:41,230 --> 00:11:41,630
Uh...

253
00:11:41,850 --> 00:11:42,640
Want some water?

254
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:46,060
Are you trying to shut me up?

255
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:47,350
Forget it.

256
00:11:47,980 --> 00:11:48,770
Hurry up.

257
00:11:49,010 --> 00:11:49,730
Wait,

258
00:11:50,020 --> 00:11:50,570
give me some water.

259
00:11:50,610 --> 00:11:52,030
I didn't say I didn't need it.

260
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:12,090
Is he gone?

261
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:16,220
Damn!

262
00:12:18,470 --> 00:12:19,840
How long have you been there?

263
00:12:19,890 --> 00:12:20,600
What's this?
You waiting for me?

264
00:12:22,970 --> 00:12:23,470
No.

265
00:12:23,770 --> 00:12:24,720
It's raining so...

266
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:25,430
So?

267
00:12:25,980 --> 00:12:27,390
I don't need an umbrella.

268
00:12:29,690 --> 00:12:30,860
I have my bike.

269
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:33,230
Don't get wet. Leave the bike here.

270
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:34,030
No,

271
00:12:35,030 --> 00:12:36,110
we have your training tomorrow.

272
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:36,780
Or,

273
00:12:37,610 --> 00:12:38,950
we could ride together.

274
00:12:39,610 --> 00:12:40,190
Together?

275
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:41,620
I mean

276
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:43,740
one of us can hold the umbrella.

277
00:12:45,250 --> 00:12:45,660
Let's go.
Fine,

278
00:12:46,660 --> 00:12:47,120
let's go.

279
00:12:48,410 --> 00:12:49,120
Go, go!

280
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:50,170
Get off.

281
00:12:50,380 --> 00:12:51,460
I'll get wet.

282
00:12:52,590 --> 00:12:53,290
No.

283
00:12:55,670 --> 00:12:56,210
Hurry up.
Hold on tight.

284
00:12:59,380 --> 00:13:00,220
It's pouring.

285
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:01,640
You bet.

286
00:13:30,540 --> 00:13:31,790
Left or right?

287
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:32,580
Which way?
Where are you going?

288
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:35,670
Lucky you, I'm taking you home.

289
00:13:35,750 --> 00:13:37,170
No, to your place.

290
00:13:37,210 --> 00:13:38,460
I need to return the favor.

291
00:13:38,510 --> 00:13:40,800
Morning at my place, afternoon at yours.

292
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:42,590
No, thanks.

293
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:43,550
Why?

294
00:13:44,050 --> 00:13:45,680
Got something hidden at home?

295
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:46,970
I just don't want to.

296
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:47,680
That's it.

297
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:50,770
Get off.

298
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,240
I feel offended.

299
00:13:59,900 --> 00:14:00,740
Sorry,

300
00:14:00,990 --> 00:14:01,900
I have my reasons.

301
00:14:02,410 --> 00:14:03,990
I'll invite you over when I'm ready.

302
00:14:04,490 --> 00:14:05,070
When?

303
00:14:05,780 --> 00:14:07,240
When it stops raining.

304
00:14:09,540 --> 00:14:10,750
That's too vague.

305
00:14:11,370 --> 00:14:12,460
Forget it. See ya.

306
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:13,670
What? Right here?

307
00:14:14,460 --> 00:14:16,130
Are you mad?

308
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:17,550
Why would I be mad?

309
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:20,010
I'm keeping my distance too.

310
00:14:20,970 --> 00:14:22,340
Take the umbrella.

311
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:36,060
I really don't know anything.

312
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:45,410
I don't need his number.

313
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:48,530
He appears like a ghost when I need him.

314
00:14:51,660 --> 00:14:53,660
Gosh, it's cold.

315
00:14:53,920 --> 00:14:54,710
Damn.

316
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,350
What's wrong?

317
00:15:29,280 --> 00:15:29,950
What?

318
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:31,040
What the hell!

319
00:15:33,660 --> 00:15:34,370
How did you...?
I mean,

320
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,750
you didn't answer so I was worried.

321
00:15:40,630 --> 00:15:41,250
Seriously?

322
00:15:42,260 --> 00:15:44,260
You always show up when I need you.

323
00:15:45,170 --> 00:15:46,470
Anyway, I'm sorry.

324
00:15:47,010 --> 00:15:47,840
I think

325
00:15:48,140 --> 00:15:49,390
you caught the cold because of me.

326
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:50,680
It wasn't because of you.

327
00:15:54,270 --> 00:15:55,350
What time is it?

328
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:56,190
Now?

329
00:15:56,730 --> 00:15:57,850
About half past eight.

330
00:16:00,570 --> 00:16:01,400
Damn it!

331
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:03,650
I'm screwed.

332
00:16:04,030 --> 00:16:04,820
I have morning training.

333
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:06,070
Forget about it.

334
00:16:06,110 --> 00:16:07,410
Rest up today,

335
00:16:07,610 --> 00:16:08,780
get better first.

336
00:16:09,570 --> 00:16:10,870
The coach will understand.

337
00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:13,240
No, it's someone else.

338
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:14,290
Who?

339
00:16:26,920 --> 00:16:27,340
Get up.

340
00:16:30,050 --> 00:16:30,930
Come on,

341
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:32,350
get up.

342
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:34,970
You want a fight?

343
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,140
Huh?

344
00:16:39,690 --> 00:16:41,690
You're not even a starter.

345
00:16:41,900 --> 00:16:44,030
The least you could do is
bring us some ice water.

346
00:16:44,070 --> 00:16:45,320
You skipped without permission?

347
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:46,110
I apologize.

348
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,450
Think about the team.

349
00:16:48,530 --> 00:16:50,070
Quit before you drag the team down.

350
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:52,120
Be smart and quit yourself.

351
00:16:52,580 --> 00:16:53,200
Got it?

352
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:55,080
I apologize.

353
00:16:56,410 --> 00:16:57,750
Nothing's changed.

354
00:16:57,790 --> 00:16:59,460
You crushed someone else's dream

355
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,250
chasing your own.

356
00:17:02,590 --> 00:17:04,340
You shameless bastard.

357
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:11,680
Wake up!

358
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:12,550
Emergency!

359
00:17:17,230 --> 00:17:18,480
You bastard! You did that on purpose!

360
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:19,020
Say it!
You did it on purpose!

361
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:28,780
Nothing to say now?

362
00:17:30,820 --> 00:17:31,530
I apologize.

363
00:17:31,660 --> 00:17:32,620
You're washed up.

364
00:17:33,910 --> 00:17:36,740
I heard you're hanging out with some weirdo.

365
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:37,790
Go see a doctor.

366
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,620
Stop dragging everyone down.

367
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:48,460
That's too harsh.

368
00:17:50,050 --> 00:17:51,050
Apologize.

369
00:17:51,180 --> 00:17:51,930
Why should I apologize?

370
00:17:52,550 --> 00:17:53,510
I didn't do anything wrong.

371
00:17:57,560 --> 00:18:00,020
I never hung out with a weirdo.

372
00:18:00,230 --> 00:18:00,940
Oh, I see.

373
00:18:01,390 --> 00:18:02,770
So now you're the weirdo?

374
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:06,860
I'll make you apologize.

375
00:18:06,900 --> 00:18:07,730
How?

376
00:18:08,530 --> 00:18:09,860
How exactly?

377
00:18:10,280 --> 00:18:12,240
If I strike you out,

378
00:18:12,610 --> 00:18:13,740
you apologize.

379
00:18:15,950 --> 00:18:17,740
You can't even throw a strike.

380
00:18:17,790 --> 00:18:19,000
How will you strike me out?

381
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:19,950
Scared?

382
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:21,460
Fine.

383
00:18:21,500 --> 00:18:22,500
If you do it,

384
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:24,290
I'll apologize. I mean it.

385
00:18:25,590 --> 00:18:26,960
But if I hit a home run,

386
00:18:28,090 --> 00:18:29,710
you quit the baseball club.

387
00:18:34,140 --> 00:18:35,430
Do you think I can beat him?

388
00:18:36,100 --> 00:18:37,180
It won't be easy.

389
00:18:38,350 --> 00:18:39,270
Will I lose?

390
00:18:39,310 --> 00:18:41,310
I think you might win,

391
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:43,940
but not now.
Why?

392
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:45,350
Why do you think so?

393
00:18:47,690 --> 00:18:50,110
You're off your game.

394
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:53,150
You can't do anything. You're off.

395
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:13,670
Let's do this.

396
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,270
Well,

397
00:19:27,230 --> 00:19:28,400
the weather is nice.

398
00:19:29,270 --> 00:19:29,820
This is brutal.

399
00:19:31,030 --> 00:19:32,740
Is this the only way?

400
00:19:32,820 --> 00:19:34,570
There's a gentler path.

401
00:19:35,030 --> 00:19:35,570
What?
You're training

402
00:19:36,530 --> 00:19:37,410
for strong legs.

403
00:19:37,740 --> 00:19:38,160
My Gosh.

404
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,280
I think it's working.

405
00:19:41,200 --> 00:19:42,540
My legs are burning.

406
00:19:43,370 --> 00:19:43,950
These hills...

407
00:19:44,410 --> 00:19:46,460
they'll increase your chances by 1%.

408
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:47,710
One percent?

409
00:19:48,380 --> 00:19:49,040
Yep.

410
00:19:49,090 --> 00:19:50,880
What do you think the chances are now?

411
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:53,510
About 30-70. Currently.

412
00:19:53,550 --> 00:19:54,720
30-70.

413
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:57,010
At-least, you know the truth clearly.

414
00:19:57,050 --> 00:19:58,840
So that 1% increase makes it...

415
00:19:59,850 --> 00:20:01,100
31 to 69.

416
00:20:02,060 --> 00:20:03,470
31 to 69?

417
00:20:13,190 --> 00:20:14,490
This is my place.

418
00:20:18,070 --> 00:20:19,200
It is far. Like you said.

419
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:20,200
But

420
00:20:20,620 --> 00:20:22,330
why did you transfer to our school?

421
00:20:22,370 --> 00:20:24,330
Because it's the only school with a baseball team.

422
00:20:24,950 --> 00:20:26,160
So it was because of me.

423
00:20:26,210 --> 00:20:27,460
Yeah. To see you.

424
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:28,000
Really?

425
00:20:28,710 --> 00:20:29,630
What do you think?

426
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:32,170
You're so full of yourself.

427
00:20:32,630 --> 00:20:34,130
You got me for a second.

428
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:35,670
Bye.

429
00:20:38,090 --> 00:20:38,970
Hey, Woo-jin!

430
00:20:40,890 --> 00:20:42,560
See? I picked a non-rainy day.

431
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:44,270
Thanks.

432
00:20:45,140 --> 00:20:45,980
Bye.

433
00:20:57,030 --> 00:20:57,950
Damn,

434
00:20:59,950 --> 00:21:00,700
my hand is numb.

435
00:21:01,320 --> 00:21:01,870
You okay?

436
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:03,740
You're pretty flexible reaching back.

437
00:21:03,780 --> 00:21:05,660
That's when there's no batter.

438
00:21:12,170 --> 00:21:12,750
Step two.

439
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:14,130
Now pitch in a game situation.

440
00:21:14,170 --> 00:21:15,000
Have a go.

441
00:21:21,010 --> 00:21:22,090
Eyes up.

442
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:24,560
You gonna pitch blind?

443
00:21:37,190 --> 00:21:37,990
I'll keep focused.

444
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:39,030
Try again.

445
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:43,990
Again.

446
00:21:44,030 --> 00:21:45,700
It's just a dummy.

447
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:46,910
One more time.

448
00:21:52,170 --> 00:21:53,210
Do your best.

449
00:21:53,540 --> 00:21:54,170
I don't know.

450
00:21:54,210 --> 00:21:55,210
What's the problem?

451
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:56,340
You know,

452
00:21:56,840 --> 00:21:58,170
your eyes wander all over the place.

453
00:21:59,130 --> 00:21:59,470
What?

454
00:21:59,510 --> 00:22:00,590
When you pitch,

455
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:03,050
you're staring at the catcher's mitt.

456
00:22:03,090 --> 00:22:04,430
The moment you release,

457
00:22:04,470 --> 00:22:06,310
your eyes start wandering.

458
00:22:07,430 --> 00:22:08,810
Eyes on my mitt.

459
00:22:09,640 --> 00:22:10,230
Got it?

460
00:22:11,940 --> 00:22:13,020
Try again.

461
00:22:18,190 --> 00:22:19,320
Eyes.

462
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:26,990
Eyes!

463
00:22:27,910 --> 00:22:28,620
That's the problem.

464
00:22:29,370 --> 00:22:29,870
Again.

465
00:22:56,690 --> 00:22:57,820
Strike!

466
00:23:09,740 --> 00:23:12,200
No wonder he won the Lee Yeong-min Batting Award.

467
00:23:12,250 --> 00:23:14,620
He has an amazing stat too.

468
00:23:15,250 --> 00:23:17,880
Only struck out ten times last season.

469
00:23:18,290 --> 00:23:19,040
Ten times?

470
00:23:20,420 --> 00:23:21,840
He's a monster.

471
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:22,630
Didn't you know?

472
00:23:23,260 --> 00:23:24,840
You're facing a monster.

473
00:23:26,220 --> 00:23:26,760
Don't worry.

474
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:29,140
I'll find a way to deal with him.

475
00:23:31,310 --> 00:23:31,970
Any footage

476
00:23:32,020 --> 00:23:33,930
of him striking out?

477
00:23:33,980 --> 00:23:35,480
You'll see some in the middle.

478
00:23:37,810 --> 00:23:41,030
More than half follow the same pattern.

479
00:23:41,070 --> 00:23:42,990
What pattern?

480
00:23:43,030 --> 00:23:44,320
High inside fastball.

481
00:23:47,320 --> 00:23:49,740
But statistically that's not his main weakness.

482
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:52,290
The key is

483
00:23:52,330 --> 00:23:54,290
how consistently I can throw it.

484
00:23:57,080 --> 00:23:57,580
Hey,

485
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:59,080
this is the final simulation test.

486
00:23:59,420 --> 00:24:01,250
Pass this, and it proves you've improved.

487
00:24:01,300 --> 00:24:02,630
Why are you wearing that uniform?

488
00:24:02,670 --> 00:24:05,220
Don't talk back to your senior.

489
00:24:07,470 --> 00:24:08,720
I found it in the laundry room.

490
00:24:08,930 --> 00:24:11,260
Jeong-ho will kill you if he catches us.

491
00:24:11,310 --> 00:24:12,930
We'll be done before he does.

492
00:24:13,060 --> 00:24:13,600
Ah!

493
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,140
I just need to throw one strike, right?

494
00:24:17,480 --> 00:24:18,980
Only if you throw it high and inside.

495
00:24:19,940 --> 00:24:20,900
What are the odds?

496
00:24:20,940 --> 00:24:22,270
Hmm...

497
00:24:22,320 --> 00:24:23,780
About 40-60.

498
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:26,700
Much better odds.

499
00:24:32,450 --> 00:24:33,080
Focus.

500
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:35,050
Your eyes wandered again.

501
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:35,980
Do it again.

502
00:24:40,580 --> 00:24:41,340
Not that one.

503
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:42,290
Again.

504
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:47,300
Pitch inside,

505
00:24:47,590 --> 00:24:48,220
nervous?
Steady.

506
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:54,140
Trust yourself. Throw it.

507
00:24:54,470 --> 00:24:55,310
You can do it.

508
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:56,140
I know.

509
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:57,600
I can do it.

510
00:24:57,980 --> 00:24:58,600
Here it comes.

511
00:25:12,450 --> 00:25:13,870
Is it 40-60 now?

512
00:25:14,450 --> 00:25:15,080
Yeah.

513
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:17,870
Let's get another 10% from luck.

514
00:25:22,290 --> 00:25:22,880
Got you!

515
00:25:23,590 --> 00:25:24,130
Yes!

516
00:25:24,750 --> 00:25:25,250
What are you doing?
What?

517
00:25:26,510 --> 00:25:27,800
You've never seen anyone pick up trash?

518
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:29,260
You're really committed.

519
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:30,930
I thought there was something behind it.

520
00:25:31,590 --> 00:25:32,010
You know,

521
00:25:32,890 --> 00:25:34,850
I'm picking up luck that others threw away.

522
00:25:34,890 --> 00:25:35,390
Huh!

523
00:25:36,890 --> 00:25:37,430
What?

524
00:25:37,470 --> 00:25:38,680
That's not my line.

525
00:25:38,930 --> 00:25:39,480
No, it's Ohtani Shohei's.

526
00:25:40,520 --> 00:25:41,230
What?
You know about that?

527
00:25:41,940 --> 00:25:43,110
Of course.

528
00:25:43,150 --> 00:25:45,480
He's the God of Baseball.
How could I not?

529
00:25:45,570 --> 00:25:46,440
It's a superstition.

530
00:25:46,860 --> 00:25:47,780
You need luck right now.
You really do.

531
00:25:48,570 --> 00:25:50,150
You picked all these for me?

532
00:25:50,490 --> 00:25:51,530
You can have them all.

533
00:25:51,780 --> 00:25:52,610
I can't take them.

534
00:25:53,030 --> 00:25:53,530
Why?

535
00:25:53,950 --> 00:25:55,410
I don't need luck.

536
00:25:55,450 --> 00:25:56,290
Wait.

537
00:25:57,790 --> 00:25:58,500
See?

538
00:25:59,370 --> 00:26:00,210
Wow!

539
00:26:01,170 --> 00:26:02,250
When did you pick these?

540
00:26:02,290 --> 00:26:04,500
Earlier, while wandering around campus.

541
00:26:04,590 --> 00:26:06,210
That's awesome.

542
00:26:06,670 --> 00:26:07,130
Still,

543
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:08,460
you take them all.

544
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:09,420
No,
I have too many.

545
00:26:09,970 --> 00:26:10,420
Take them.
I said no.

546
00:26:11,010 --> 00:26:12,260
I don't need luck.

547
00:26:12,300 --> 00:26:12,840
Take them.

548
00:26:12,890 --> 00:26:14,890
Wait.

549
00:26:15,300 --> 00:26:17,010
Want to test

550
00:26:17,260 --> 00:26:19,100
if luck is on your side?

551
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:20,310
How?

552
00:26:22,850 --> 00:26:23,400
Watch this.

553
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:25,690
Pick one up.

554
00:26:26,980 --> 00:26:27,610
Get ready.

555
00:26:28,360 --> 00:26:29,490
Throw it in the trash can.

556
00:26:32,950 --> 00:26:33,780
Then you'll win.

557
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:36,870
Damn,

558
00:26:37,160 --> 00:26:38,540
so close.

559
00:26:39,370 --> 00:26:39,950
Your turn.

560
00:26:41,790 --> 00:26:42,580
I'll win.

561
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:45,580
Hey.

562
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:48,090
I said win, you should say lose.

563
00:26:48,300 --> 00:26:48,920
Again.

564
00:26:49,380 --> 00:26:50,130
I'll win.

565
00:26:52,300 --> 00:26:53,550
Follow the rules.

566
00:26:53,590 --> 00:26:55,090
I don't want to say that word.

567
00:26:56,260 --> 00:26:56,930
I'll win.

568
00:26:58,350 --> 00:26:59,810
It's just for fun. It's a game.

569
00:27:00,060 --> 00:27:00,850
Game.

570
00:27:01,430 --> 00:27:02,560
I'll win.

571
00:27:05,150 --> 00:27:07,230
Can't even take a joke with this blockhead.

572
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:08,860
I have to win tomorrow.

573
00:27:09,730 --> 00:27:11,740
I need to make Jeong-ho apologize.

574
00:27:12,240 --> 00:27:13,150
For what?

575
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:15,700
He can badmouth me,

576
00:27:15,990 --> 00:27:18,620
but I won't let him badmouth you.

577
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:20,580
Absolutely not?

578
00:27:21,330 --> 00:27:21,950
Does he know me?
Tae-hui,

579
00:27:22,620 --> 00:27:24,410
he called you a weirdo.

580
00:27:24,460 --> 00:27:26,790
Is that why you challenged him?

581
00:27:27,210 --> 00:27:27,880
Of course.

582
00:27:29,590 --> 00:27:30,300
Alright.

583
00:27:31,090 --> 00:27:31,920
Please do win!

584
00:27:33,050 --> 00:27:34,010
I will win.

585
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:03,200
Ready?

586
00:28:06,210 --> 00:28:07,120
Shall we go?

587
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:15,550
Rules are simple.

588
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:17,630
Pitcher strikes out the batter, pitcher wins.

589
00:28:18,260 --> 00:28:20,260
Batter hits a home run, batter wins.

590
00:28:20,850 --> 00:28:23,180
What if he keeps pitching to the corners?

591
00:28:23,310 --> 00:28:24,430
That won't happen.

592
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,230
If the pitcher intentionally avoids the strike zone,

593
00:28:26,270 --> 00:28:30,020
the umpire will call a forfeit.

594
00:28:30,060 --> 00:28:30,770
Satisfied?

595
00:28:31,150 --> 00:28:31,730
Alright.
Okay.

596
00:28:33,150 --> 00:28:34,690
If you want to run, run now.

597
00:28:35,130 --> 00:28:36,950
This is the last time I help you as your senior.

598
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:39,160
Sorry.

599
00:28:39,490 --> 00:28:41,450
but this junior of yours doesn't need any help.

600
00:28:41,730 --> 00:28:42,420
You bastard!

601
00:28:42,520 --> 00:28:43,710
I'll make you apologize.

602
00:28:45,850 --> 00:28:46,880
I will crush you!

603
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:09,940
Play ball!

604
00:29:32,380 --> 00:29:33,210
Ball!

605
00:29:55,940 --> 00:29:56,780
Two balls!

606
00:29:57,860 --> 00:29:58,490
Ah...

607
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:19,670
Almost took my head off.

608
00:30:21,930 --> 00:30:22,470
Three balls!

609
00:30:25,050 --> 00:30:25,470
Damn.

610
00:30:25,970 --> 00:30:26,810
Crazy.

611
00:30:28,220 --> 00:30:29,270
This is your last at-bat.

612
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:31,140
Get ready to clear out your locker.

613
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:10,100
Tae-hui,

614
00:31:11,350 --> 00:31:12,600
you can't be here.

615
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:14,480
You looked lonely out here by yourself.

616
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:15,270
I see.
Get out now.

617
00:31:16,150 --> 00:31:18,070
Don't be like that. I'm your manager now.

618
00:31:19,980 --> 00:31:20,440
What?

619
00:31:20,690 --> 00:31:21,570
What the hell is he doing?
What?

620
00:31:22,780 --> 00:31:24,360
I came to support my pitcher.

621
00:31:25,610 --> 00:31:27,780
You have another pitcher?

622
00:31:28,240 --> 00:31:28,660
Yeah.

623
00:31:28,700 --> 00:31:29,870
Time for a change.

624
00:31:30,410 --> 00:31:30,870
To who?

625
00:31:31,870 --> 00:31:32,910
Woo-jin 2.0.

626
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:33,710
What?

627
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:35,170
You're back to square one.

628
00:31:35,210 --> 00:31:36,040
Think about it.

629
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:37,830
Where did all that luck

630
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:39,130
and effort go?

631
00:31:39,420 --> 00:31:39,920
Huh?
What?

632
00:31:40,590 --> 00:31:41,960
Did you reboot or something?

633
00:31:42,770 --> 00:31:43,290
No,

634
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:49,760
I still have it.

635
00:31:49,810 --> 00:31:51,430
Then you're still Woo-jin 2.0.

636
00:31:53,480 --> 00:31:54,100
Hey!
Aren't you going to pitch?

637
00:31:55,100 --> 00:31:55,890
Leave him be.

638
00:31:56,940 --> 00:31:59,020
It's time for his last prayer.

639
00:31:59,060 --> 00:31:59,820
Give it everything.

640
00:32:00,270 --> 00:32:00,980
Okay!

641
00:32:02,150 --> 00:32:03,820
You promised you'd win.

642
00:32:04,110 --> 00:32:04,440
Okay.

643
00:32:05,030 --> 00:32:06,780
I'll win.

644
00:32:12,540 --> 00:32:13,290
Play ball!

645
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:45,440
Strike!

646
00:32:45,490 --> 00:32:45,940
Strike!

647
00:32:54,410 --> 00:32:55,700
Strike!

648
00:32:56,830 --> 00:32:58,460
You got the speed gun?

649
00:32:58,620 --> 00:32:59,170
What?

650
00:32:59,500 --> 00:33:00,250
Yeah.

651
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:04,460
Now the real game starts.

652
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:06,630
It's just one strike. Don't get cocky.

653
00:33:07,340 --> 00:33:09,090
Why would I? It's just one strike.

654
00:33:09,130 --> 00:33:10,050
Throw another one.

655
00:33:10,090 --> 00:33:11,800
You'll never throw another strike.

656
00:33:12,350 --> 00:33:14,100
Let's see who laughs last.

657
00:33:14,260 --> 00:33:15,850
Stop talking and throw.

658
00:33:20,150 --> 00:33:21,230
Throw a changeup.

659
00:33:22,020 --> 00:33:23,190
He'll think it's a fastball.

660
00:33:35,910 --> 00:33:36,580
Alas.

661
00:33:39,580 --> 00:33:40,750
A changeup?

662
00:33:40,790 --> 00:33:42,250
You think I can't hit that?

663
00:33:43,710 --> 00:33:45,340
Throw it.

664
00:33:45,380 --> 00:33:47,130
I'll hit it the other way.

665
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:51,300
Now, high inside fastball.

666
00:34:02,650 --> 00:34:03,230
He hit it.

667
00:34:06,150 --> 00:34:06,530
You're done!
Wow!

668
00:34:07,610 --> 00:34:08,490
Did it go out?

669
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:11,320
No, it bounced,

670
00:34:11,910 --> 00:34:12,740
didn't go out.
Damn!

671
00:34:13,700 --> 00:34:14,910
Ground rule double.

672
00:34:15,490 --> 00:34:16,200
It's a tie.

673
00:34:18,330 --> 00:34:19,200
Lucky you.

674
00:34:23,580 --> 00:34:24,790
Let's go.

675
00:34:35,100 --> 00:34:36,010
Sorry.

676
00:34:38,390 --> 00:34:39,470
I really wanted to win.

677
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:43,600
Congratulations.

678
00:34:43,650 --> 00:34:44,980
You threw a strike.

679
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:46,400
Well done.

680
00:35:01,870 --> 00:35:02,580
Yummy.

681
00:35:04,580 --> 00:35:06,000
You want a burger?

682
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:08,250
This ketchup is making me hungry.

683
00:35:08,670 --> 00:35:10,920
Isn't this too humble for a celebration?

684
00:35:10,960 --> 00:35:12,170
What's wrong with a burger?

685
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:15,050
I didn't win anyway, so...

686
00:35:15,090 --> 00:35:16,720
But you achieved your goal anyway.

687
00:35:16,890 --> 00:35:18,010
Yeah, I did, but...

688
00:35:18,930 --> 00:35:19,890
By the way,

689
00:35:21,220 --> 00:35:22,350
about that last pitch...

690
00:35:22,480 --> 00:35:22,930
Go ahead.

691
00:35:23,640 --> 00:35:25,020
Technically, that was an out.

692
00:35:25,650 --> 00:35:26,980
In a real game,

693
00:35:27,020 --> 00:35:28,400
that would be a fly out to center.

694
00:35:29,320 --> 00:35:29,940
Come on,

695
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:32,190
center fielders aren't supermen.

696
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:34,610
It's impossible. I was just lucky.

697
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:36,070
You weren't lucky.

698
00:35:36,990 --> 00:35:38,240
He was overpowered.

699
00:35:38,830 --> 00:35:39,490
Come on,

700
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:41,540
you're flattering me.

701
00:35:41,580 --> 00:35:42,500
I didn't say that.

702
00:35:42,950 --> 00:35:43,460
Who did then?

703
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:45,750
I overheard the coaches talking.

704
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:50,420
A 153km/h high inside fastball. The batter was slow.

705
00:35:51,550 --> 00:35:52,090
Really?

706
00:35:52,130 --> 00:35:53,210
Why would I lie?

707
00:36:00,310 --> 00:36:01,060
Are you happy?

708
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:03,480
Happy.

709
00:36:05,060 --> 00:36:05,600
Thanks.

710
00:36:05,980 --> 00:36:06,730
It's all thanks to you.

711
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:08,730
You don't need a manager anymore.

712
00:36:08,860 --> 00:36:09,690
What do you mean?

713
00:36:09,730 --> 00:36:10,940
We're going to be together forever.

714
00:36:10,980 --> 00:36:12,650
I feel like my job is done.

715
00:36:13,320 --> 00:36:13,900
Shut up.

716
00:36:13,990 --> 00:36:15,450
What are you doing after school tomorrow?

717
00:36:15,610 --> 00:36:16,030
Tomorrow?
Yeah.

718
00:36:17,110 --> 00:36:17,990
Nothing special. Why?
I need to go somewhere.

719
00:36:18,740 --> 00:36:19,280
Come with me.
With you?

720
00:36:20,120 --> 00:36:20,660
Why?

721
00:36:20,700 --> 00:36:23,540
Since I can throw strikes again,

722
00:36:24,160 --> 00:36:26,160
I need to meet someone.

723
00:36:32,130 --> 00:36:33,460
You're the manager now.

724
00:36:33,510 --> 00:36:34,550
Got any plans?

725
00:36:41,350 --> 00:36:42,640
You're totally obsessed.

726
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:44,060
Now pitch in a game situation.

727
00:36:47,390 --> 00:36:48,940
Eyes on the catcher's mitt.

728
00:36:49,690 --> 00:36:50,730
You can do it.

729
00:36:52,270 --> 00:36:53,320
Strike!

730
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:58,990
I have a new goal.

731
00:37:07,750 --> 00:37:09,000
Who are we going to meet?

732
00:37:09,370 --> 00:37:09,960
Huh?

733
00:37:12,750 --> 00:37:13,250
I ruined

734
00:37:13,590 --> 00:37:15,260
someone's dream.

735
00:37:15,460 --> 00:37:17,550
That happens all the time in baseball.

736
00:37:17,800 --> 00:37:19,970
But that doesn't change what I did.

737
00:37:37,650 --> 00:37:38,280
We're here.

738
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,240
Is this your first time here?

739
00:37:41,240 --> 00:37:42,570
No, I came once before.

740
00:37:47,500 --> 00:37:48,540
That's when I realized

741
00:37:49,580 --> 00:37:51,670
I had destroyed someone's dream.

742
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:05,890
Lower your center.

743
00:38:11,020 --> 00:38:11,810
Good.

744
00:38:18,530 --> 00:38:19,650
Focus,

745
00:38:25,160 --> 00:38:26,120
Jeong-ho.

746
00:38:26,740 --> 00:38:27,450
I said focus.

747
00:38:27,980 --> 00:38:28,760
Posture.

748
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:44,590
Don't come here, you little punk.

749
00:38:45,010 --> 00:38:45,890
Listen...

750
00:38:45,930 --> 00:38:47,140
Get lost, or I'll make you get lost.

751
00:38:50,310 --> 00:38:50,810
You want a fight?

752
00:38:51,020 --> 00:38:52,440
I want to see Tae-seop.

753
00:38:52,590 --> 00:38:53,220
Get lost.

754
00:38:53,270 --> 00:38:54,900
Tae-seop's not coming back.

755
00:38:55,690 --> 00:38:56,900
What do you mean?

756
00:38:56,940 --> 00:38:58,320
You drove him away.

757
00:38:58,360 --> 00:38:59,440
It's you who

758
00:38:59,690 --> 00:39:01,610
you made him give up baseball! Bastard!

759
00:39:13,540 --> 00:39:14,290
Thank you.

760
00:39:22,880 --> 00:39:23,590
Got anything?

761
00:39:25,470 --> 00:39:26,850
They understood,

762
00:39:27,100 --> 00:39:28,510
but Tae-seop's address is confidential.

763
00:39:29,100 --> 00:39:30,350
They couldn't tell me.

764
00:39:31,470 --> 00:39:32,310
I see.

765
00:39:37,610 --> 00:39:39,190
What do you want to say to him?

766
00:39:40,070 --> 00:39:41,570
Well,

767
00:39:41,610 --> 00:39:43,400
I want to ask him

768
00:39:43,740 --> 00:39:46,820
if I can keep playing baseball.

769
00:39:46,990 --> 00:39:47,570
Hey!

770
00:39:48,530 --> 00:39:49,700
why ask that?

771
00:39:50,370 --> 00:39:51,700
You want his permission?

772
00:39:51,740 --> 00:39:53,580
Not permission, but...

773
00:39:53,620 --> 00:39:55,000
If Tae-seop hated the thought

774
00:39:55,040 --> 00:39:57,000
of you playing baseball, would you quit?

775
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:58,420
Of course not.

776
00:39:58,460 --> 00:40:00,750
See? You finally get to play the way you want.

777
00:40:00,800 --> 00:40:01,880
If he disapproves,

778
00:40:02,300 --> 00:40:03,630
would you go back to him?

779
00:40:03,670 --> 00:40:05,340
Who said anything about going back?

780
00:40:05,380 --> 00:40:06,680
Then why ask?

781
00:40:06,720 --> 00:40:08,180
I've never apologized.

782
00:40:08,220 --> 00:40:09,430
You don't need to apologize.

783
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:10,220
What?

784
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:14,600
You can't see him, and he probably doesn't wanna see you.

785
00:40:16,900 --> 00:40:18,770
Look, the sky's right there.

786
00:40:19,110 --> 00:40:21,480
Just yell I'm sorry and move on.

787
00:40:21,570 --> 00:40:22,190
Damn it!

788
00:40:24,900 --> 00:40:26,070
Are you really that heartless?

789
00:40:27,110 --> 00:40:28,160
He'll hear it.

790
00:40:30,870 --> 00:40:31,990
You're the worst.

791
00:40:33,870 --> 00:40:34,290
Hey!
Hey!

792
00:40:35,710 --> 00:40:36,710
Where are you going?

793
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,000
Never mind.

794
00:40:39,040 --> 00:40:40,710
I have nothing to say to you.

795
00:41:15,910 --> 00:41:18,500
Leaving me behind, you're so petty.

796
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:38,060
Have you seen Tae-hui?

797
00:41:38,180 --> 00:41:38,850
Tae-hui?

798
00:41:39,350 --> 00:41:40,270
No.

799
00:41:40,850 --> 00:41:43,270
Any idea where he might be?

800
00:41:44,190 --> 00:41:45,610
But who is Tae-hui?

801
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:48,900
You know, the transfer student from last week.

802
00:41:49,030 --> 00:41:49,860
That transfer student?

803
00:41:50,950 --> 00:41:51,660
Over there.

804
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:53,030
Jeong-won!

805
00:41:53,830 --> 00:41:54,580
Park Jeong-won!

806
00:41:58,370 --> 00:41:59,080
Yeah?

807
00:42:01,080 --> 00:42:03,750
Did anyone else transfer here?

808
00:42:04,540 --> 00:42:06,050
Just him.

809
00:42:17,930 --> 00:42:19,060
My name is Tae-hui.

810
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:20,270
Kwon Tae-hui.

811
00:42:20,310 --> 00:42:21,730
I've never heard of you.

812
00:42:21,770 --> 00:42:22,400
I just transferred here.

813
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:23,770
Oh, yeah?

814
00:42:50,170 --> 00:42:51,300
What are you wandering around for?

815
00:42:52,130 --> 00:42:53,010
What are you looking for?

816
00:42:53,340 --> 00:42:54,970
Tae-hui.

817
00:42:55,010 --> 00:42:57,100
A friend I just met.

818
00:42:57,140 --> 00:42:57,930
Have you seen him?

819
00:42:58,720 --> 00:43:00,060
You have a friend named Tae-hui?

820
00:43:03,390 --> 00:43:04,190
Where is he now?

821
00:43:05,150 --> 00:43:05,690
Wait,

822
00:43:07,070 --> 00:43:08,400
you saw Tae-hui.

823
00:43:09,190 --> 00:43:09,900
When?

824
00:43:10,400 --> 00:43:12,200
During my match with Jeong-ho.

825
00:43:12,240 --> 00:43:14,280
He was on the mound for a bit.

826
00:43:14,700 --> 00:43:16,030
You can't stay here.

827
00:43:16,070 --> 00:43:17,530
You looked lonely out here by yourself.

828
00:43:20,240 --> 00:43:20,950
Really?

829
00:43:24,120 --> 00:43:25,710
I recorded the match.

830
00:43:25,750 --> 00:43:27,750
Let me see when he appeared on the mound.

831
00:43:30,460 --> 00:43:31,260
Wait.

832
00:43:33,590 --> 00:43:34,430
Was that real?

833
00:43:48,770 --> 00:43:49,820
Who was he talking to?

834
00:43:50,070 --> 00:43:50,650
Who cares?

835
00:43:50,690 --> 00:43:52,360
Probably an imaginary friend.

836
00:43:53,900 --> 00:43:54,780
Tae-hui is

837
00:43:55,570 --> 00:43:56,990
invisible.

838
00:44:21,100 --> 00:44:21,930
Kwon Yong-jae.

839
00:44:23,520 --> 00:44:25,020
That must be Tae-hui's dad.

840
00:44:26,310 --> 00:44:27,560
Apartment 1305.

841
00:44:50,920 --> 00:44:51,590
Who is it?

842
00:44:52,710 --> 00:44:53,670
Hello?

843
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:55,880
I'm a friend of Tae-hui's from school.

844
00:44:57,550 --> 00:44:58,470
Who?

845
00:44:59,050 --> 00:44:59,970
Tae-hui.

846
00:45:00,430 --> 00:45:02,050
Is Tae-hui home?

847
00:45:11,060 --> 00:45:12,110
Hello,

848
00:45:12,570 --> 00:45:16,320
I had plans with Tae-hee but can't reach him.

849
00:45:18,700 --> 00:45:19,910
Who?

850
00:45:19,950 --> 00:45:20,240
Who?
Tae-hui.

851
00:45:21,160 --> 00:45:22,120
Kwon Tae-hui.

852
00:45:22,660 --> 00:45:24,410
You made plans to meet Tae-hui?

853
00:45:25,080 --> 00:45:25,450
Yeah.

854
00:45:27,460 --> 00:45:29,080
How do you know Tae-hui?

855
00:45:29,120 --> 00:45:30,830
I'm his friend from school.

856
00:45:31,540 --> 00:45:32,670
From school?

857
00:45:32,710 --> 00:45:33,590
Middle school?

858
00:45:33,920 --> 00:45:34,880
No.

859
00:45:34,920 --> 00:45:36,550
High school.

860
00:45:38,670 --> 00:45:40,590
Tae-hui didn't come to school today.

861
00:45:42,050 --> 00:45:42,600
Then

862
00:45:43,800 --> 00:45:46,310
you saw him yesterday?

863
00:45:46,600 --> 00:45:48,310
Yes, I was with him yesterday.

864
00:45:59,990 --> 00:46:00,950
Thank you.

865
00:46:08,580 --> 00:46:10,830
Do you play baseball too?

866
00:46:11,290 --> 00:46:11,920
Yes,

867
00:46:12,420 --> 00:46:13,420
but how did you...?

868
00:46:13,960 --> 00:46:14,960
What's your name?

869
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:16,340
I'm Lee Woo-jin.

870
00:46:18,760 --> 00:46:20,880
Tae-hui is my manager.

871
00:46:21,840 --> 00:46:22,840
Your manager?

872
00:46:22,890 --> 00:46:23,340
Yes.

873
00:46:23,390 --> 00:46:25,510
Tae-hui just appeared out of nowhere

874
00:46:25,850 --> 00:46:27,770
and offered to be my manager.

875
00:46:28,100 --> 00:46:31,600
Since then, we trained together every day.

876
00:46:31,940 --> 00:46:32,810
We ate together.

877
00:46:33,440 --> 00:46:34,770
We went to school together.

878
00:46:36,190 --> 00:46:37,150
It seems

879
00:46:38,150 --> 00:46:40,240
Tae-hui finally came to see you.

880
00:46:41,490 --> 00:46:43,320
It's hard to believe,

881
00:46:43,950 --> 00:46:46,080
but it doesn't sound like you're lying.

882
00:46:46,120 --> 00:46:46,620
No,

883
00:46:46,870 --> 00:46:48,540
I'm not lying.

884
00:46:51,410 --> 00:46:53,250
I'm glad you came before it was too late.

885
00:46:53,500 --> 00:46:53,960
What?

886
00:46:54,290 --> 00:46:55,290
What do you mean?

887
00:46:57,420 --> 00:46:57,920
Should we

888
00:46:58,250 --> 00:46:59,960
go see Tae-hui now?

889
00:47:03,470 --> 00:47:05,390
Is Tae-hui home?

890
00:47:07,220 --> 00:47:09,600
Actually, Tae-hui is his nickname at home.

891
00:47:10,350 --> 00:47:10,810
So

892
00:47:12,180 --> 00:47:14,270
Tae-hui isn't his real name.

893
00:47:15,060 --> 00:47:17,610
His grandfather gave him that name,

894
00:47:18,190 --> 00:47:19,900
but he said it sounded too old.

895
00:47:20,900 --> 00:47:21,650
Tae-seop.

896
00:47:21,690 --> 00:47:22,900
He's Kwon Tae-seop.

897
00:47:25,320 --> 00:47:26,120
Tae-seop?

898
00:47:27,120 --> 00:47:29,540
If he called himself Tae-hui,

899
00:47:29,830 --> 00:47:31,450
I'm sure he was trying to hide his identity.

900
00:47:33,370 --> 00:47:34,710
Kwon Tae-seop?

901
00:47:37,960 --> 00:47:38,880
Here.

902
00:47:58,520 --> 00:47:59,190
Tae-seop.
Yes!

903
00:48:00,190 --> 00:48:00,980
Focus.

904
00:48:02,190 --> 00:48:02,690
One hit.

905
00:48:03,240 --> 00:48:03,570
Okay!
Off you go.

906
00:48:07,700 --> 00:48:09,830
One hit ties the game.

907
00:48:12,160 --> 00:48:12,950
You can do it!
Come on!

908
00:48:14,830 --> 00:48:15,290
You can do it!

909
00:48:35,850 --> 00:48:36,190
No!

910
00:48:37,060 --> 00:48:37,400
Oh my god!

911
00:48:38,190 --> 00:48:38,690
Oh, no!
Where did it hit him?

912
00:48:48,160 --> 00:48:49,740
I'm sorry I found out so late.

913
00:48:51,580 --> 00:48:53,120
I'm so sorry.

914
00:48:54,950 --> 00:48:57,000
He looks completely different now.

915
00:48:57,790 --> 00:48:59,420
He even hid his name.

916
00:48:59,750 --> 00:49:01,630
Of course, you wouldn't know.

917
00:49:02,960 --> 00:49:03,670
But

918
00:49:04,800 --> 00:49:05,970
of all people,

919
00:49:06,220 --> 00:49:07,010
it was Tae-seop.

920
00:49:07,680 --> 00:49:10,180
He was the Tae-seop I'd been looking for.

921
00:49:10,590 --> 00:49:11,800
Don't blame yourself.

922
00:49:13,100 --> 00:49:15,270
If Tae-hui wanted to reveal himself,

923
00:49:15,850 --> 00:49:17,770
he wouldn't have hidden his name.

924
00:49:19,060 --> 00:49:19,730
He

925
00:49:21,060 --> 00:49:23,610
never blamed you.

926
00:49:24,190 --> 00:49:26,530
But I destroyed his dream.

927
00:49:26,740 --> 00:49:27,360
No,

928
00:49:28,320 --> 00:49:30,700
you didn't steal his dream.

929
00:49:32,070 --> 00:49:32,490
What?

930
00:49:32,910 --> 00:49:33,910
I don't understand.

931
00:49:48,920 --> 00:49:49,590
Play ball!

932
00:49:57,430 --> 00:49:58,230
Pitcher!

933
00:49:59,060 --> 00:49:59,810
Come on!

934
00:50:07,860 --> 00:50:08,690
Lee Woo-jin!
What the hell!

935
00:50:09,650 --> 00:50:10,320
Hey!
That idiot!

936
00:50:11,320 --> 00:50:11,740
Hey!
Are you crazy?

937
00:50:37,010 --> 00:50:38,350
Where am I?

938
00:50:39,140 --> 00:50:39,730
You're awake.

939
00:50:40,390 --> 00:50:41,060
Are you okay?

940
00:50:41,940 --> 00:50:42,520
Mom.
The game,

941
00:50:43,980 --> 00:50:45,270
how did it go?

942
00:50:45,810 --> 00:50:48,360
You just woke up. Seriously?

943
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:49,740
What was the result of the game?

944
00:50:51,030 --> 00:50:52,200
I don't know.

945
00:50:56,450 --> 00:50:58,160
The MRI results are back.

946
00:50:58,580 --> 00:51:00,290
The concussion isn't severe.

947
00:51:00,330 --> 00:51:01,500
Thank goodness.

948
00:51:02,830 --> 00:51:03,170
But

949
00:51:04,210 --> 00:51:06,670
I don't know if it's lucky or unlucky.

950
00:51:07,340 --> 00:51:09,510
We found a brain tumor on the scan.

951
00:51:10,380 --> 00:51:10,920
What?

952
00:51:11,130 --> 00:51:12,550
Found early.

953
00:51:13,050 --> 00:51:14,050
There's hope.

954
00:51:14,590 --> 00:51:15,220
Can I

955
00:51:16,140 --> 00:51:17,810
still play baseball?

956
00:51:19,600 --> 00:51:22,600
Further scans showed it had spread.

957
00:51:23,440 --> 00:51:25,690
The doctors said Tae-hui had at most one year left.

958
00:51:26,440 --> 00:51:28,570
If we hadn't found the tumor,

959
00:51:29,070 --> 00:51:30,780
we wouldn't

960
00:51:31,320 --> 00:51:33,530
have had even that one year.

961
00:51:34,360 --> 00:51:35,160
And

962
00:51:35,610 --> 00:51:38,080
Tae-hui lived for over four years.

963
00:51:38,580 --> 00:51:39,910
I still believe

964
00:51:40,410 --> 00:51:42,960
that was thanks to you.

965
00:51:45,420 --> 00:51:47,670
But I didn't do anything.

966
00:52:03,180 --> 00:52:04,440
What's this?

967
00:52:04,890 --> 00:52:07,400
This is

968
00:52:07,900 --> 00:52:09,150
the time you gave Tae-hui.

969
00:52:29,000 --> 00:52:30,710
Why didn't you get treatment?

970
00:52:31,170 --> 00:52:32,760
Because you couldn't play baseball anymore?

971
00:52:35,970 --> 00:52:37,680
Why are you talking to me?

972
00:52:40,800 --> 00:52:44,140
Lee Woo-jin loses control in the final.

973
00:52:45,390 --> 00:52:49,480
He's thrown 20 consecutive balls.

974
00:52:56,780 --> 00:52:59,530
Coach comes out to change pitchers.

975
00:53:00,120 --> 00:53:02,740
Why suddenly can't he throw strikes?

976
00:53:04,120 --> 00:53:08,250
Some call this kind of sudden condition a yip.

977
00:53:08,870 --> 00:53:12,170
Sometimes players just can't perform,

978
00:53:12,210 --> 00:53:13,090
it happens.

979
00:53:14,590 --> 00:53:17,010
-Because of that accident...
-Mom, I

980
00:53:17,970 --> 00:53:19,220
I want to get treatment.

981
00:53:19,510 --> 00:53:19,970
What?

982
00:53:46,160 --> 00:53:46,910
Why?

983
00:53:46,950 --> 00:53:48,750
I want to learn how to overcome the yips.

984
00:54:19,650 --> 00:54:21,740
The yips are psychological.

985
00:54:22,490 --> 00:54:25,950
but if you believe you can recover, it's possible.

986
00:54:39,420 --> 00:54:40,760
Are you planning to

987
00:54:41,720 --> 00:54:43,430
see Woo-jin once you're better.

988
00:54:44,510 --> 00:54:45,140
Yes.

989
00:54:46,390 --> 00:54:48,430
I wanna help him throw strikes again.

990
00:55:12,790 --> 00:55:16,250
So Tae-hui cared about me that much.

991
00:55:22,130 --> 00:55:26,390
Tae-hui was eager to get better quickly to see you.

992
00:55:28,060 --> 00:55:29,560
He didn't get better,

993
00:55:30,970 --> 00:55:32,980
but I'm glad he got to see you.

994
00:55:48,410 --> 00:55:49,950
Tae-hui made this for you.

995
00:55:53,750 --> 00:55:55,170
Thank you.

996
00:55:55,500 --> 00:55:56,460
You should

997
00:55:57,170 --> 00:55:58,880
thank Tae-hui.

998
00:55:59,380 --> 00:56:01,090
He made it.

999
00:56:16,940 --> 00:56:19,980
Should we let Tae-hui go now?

1000
00:56:20,650 --> 00:56:21,940
What do you mean?

1001
00:56:23,240 --> 00:56:23,900
I think

1002
00:56:25,200 --> 00:56:26,950
for the past 49 days,

1003
00:56:26,990 --> 00:56:30,160
we might have been holding him back.

1004
00:56:32,200 --> 00:56:34,540
But at least you saw him.

1005
00:56:34,580 --> 00:56:37,290
When does the mourning end?

1006
00:56:39,250 --> 00:56:40,340
Tonight.

1007
00:56:41,460 --> 00:56:43,090
Tonight?

1008
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:50,430
I haven't even

1009
00:56:51,010 --> 00:56:53,270
said a proper goodbye to Tae-hui.

1010
00:56:54,850 --> 00:56:58,020
He might still be waiting somewhere.

1011
00:56:59,020 --> 00:57:01,520
You know where, right?

1012
00:57:13,660 --> 00:57:14,120
Home run!

1013
00:57:14,910 --> 00:57:15,290
Who are you?

1014
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:16,540
Me?
Yeah, you.

1015
00:57:19,000 --> 00:57:19,790
Interesting.
What's interesting?

1016
00:57:21,880 --> 00:57:22,790
I won't tell you.

1017
00:57:22,840 --> 00:57:24,590
I told you to stay away from me.

1018
00:57:24,630 --> 00:57:26,550
I thought you couldn't see me.

1019
00:57:26,720 --> 00:57:27,510
Are you a ghost?

1020
00:57:28,760 --> 00:57:30,260
You always appear out of nowhere.

1021
00:57:31,680 --> 00:57:32,930
Kwon Tae-hui!

1022
00:57:38,060 --> 00:57:39,020
Where are you?

1023
00:57:42,810 --> 00:57:43,770
Where are you?

1024
00:57:48,280 --> 00:57:49,990
You can't keep hiding from me.

1025
00:57:50,740 --> 00:57:51,530
Why not?

1026
00:57:52,070 --> 00:57:53,530
Got something hidden at home?

1027
00:57:53,580 --> 00:57:54,830
I just don't want to.

1028
00:57:55,120 --> 00:57:55,700
That's it.

1029
00:57:57,660 --> 00:57:58,710
You don't need a manager anymore.

1030
00:57:58,790 --> 00:57:59,580
What do you mean?

1031
00:57:59,670 --> 00:58:00,790
We're going to be together forever.

1032
00:58:00,870 --> 00:58:02,670
I feel like my job is done.

1033
00:58:03,000 --> 00:58:04,880
Look, the sky's right there.

1034
00:58:05,210 --> 00:58:07,630
Just yell I'm sorry and move on.

1035
00:58:07,760 --> 00:58:08,550
Damn.

1036
00:58:09,510 --> 00:58:10,630
Are you really that heartless?

1037
00:58:11,590 --> 00:58:12,720
He'll hear it.

1038
00:58:15,390 --> 00:58:16,810
Stop hiding. Come out.

1039
00:58:25,360 --> 00:58:26,190
Tae-hui,

1040
00:58:28,440 --> 00:58:28,990
come out!

1041
00:58:35,740 --> 00:58:37,290
Come out! Now!

1042
00:58:45,540 --> 00:58:46,500
Come out! Now!

1043
00:58:49,630 --> 00:58:50,010
Damn!

1044
00:58:50,300 --> 00:58:51,590
Foul ball!

1045
00:58:52,130 --> 00:58:52,880
Good pitch!

1046
00:58:55,600 --> 00:58:56,220
What?

1047
00:58:56,640 --> 00:58:57,600
Weren't you looking for me?

1048
00:58:59,930 --> 00:59:00,230
Tae-hui,

1049
00:59:00,850 --> 00:59:02,480
what took you so long?

1050
00:59:02,980 --> 00:59:05,190
You didn't look like you wanted to talk.

1051
00:59:05,230 --> 00:59:05,980
I was just frustrated.

1052
00:59:06,020 --> 00:59:07,320
Lost my temper.

1053
00:59:08,860 --> 00:59:10,110
Why didn't you tell me?

1054
00:59:10,240 --> 00:59:12,400
At first, I didn't want to.

1055
00:59:13,570 --> 00:59:15,870
I thought you wouldn't notice me.

1056
00:59:16,280 --> 00:59:18,990
How long were you planning to hide it?

1057
00:59:19,490 --> 00:59:20,500
Until

1058
00:59:20,950 --> 00:59:21,620
I couldn't anymore.

1059
00:59:22,580 --> 00:59:24,710
I was gonna tell you after I was gone.

1060
00:59:24,750 --> 00:59:25,830
Why would you do that?

1061
00:59:26,590 --> 00:59:28,800
I didn't want you to

1062
00:59:28,960 --> 00:59:31,380
find out I was dead.

1063
00:59:32,420 --> 00:59:33,010
And

1064
00:59:33,470 --> 00:59:34,970
if you knew,

1065
00:59:35,010 --> 00:59:37,010
you'd panic and give up baseball.

1066
00:59:37,050 --> 00:59:39,470
Do you think I'm that fragile?

1067
00:59:39,770 --> 00:59:41,020
I thought so back then.

1068
00:59:41,060 --> 00:59:42,680
Do you still think so now?

1069
00:59:42,730 --> 00:59:43,100
No,
not anymore.

1070
00:59:44,440 --> 00:59:46,020
I just wanna help you

1071
00:59:46,190 --> 00:59:47,520
before I go.

1072
00:59:48,230 --> 00:59:48,980
That's all.

1073
00:59:51,570 --> 00:59:52,940
When are you leaving?

1074
00:59:54,150 --> 00:59:55,820
Can't we just stay like this?

1075
00:59:57,200 --> 00:59:58,080
No.

1076
00:59:58,120 --> 00:59:59,120
Why the hell not?

1077
00:59:59,200 --> 00:59:59,580
Hey!
Are you saying

1078
01:00:00,700 --> 01:00:03,290
I should wander the earth as a ghost?

1079
01:00:04,540 --> 01:00:05,670
That's not what I meant.

1080
01:00:07,460 --> 01:00:09,170
When exactly are you leaving?

1081
01:00:09,920 --> 01:00:10,380
Soon.

1082
01:00:10,460 --> 01:00:12,590
How soon is soon?

1083
01:00:13,800 --> 01:00:15,050
I said soon.

1084
01:00:26,390 --> 01:00:27,020
Hey.

1085
01:00:27,230 --> 01:00:28,520
are you gonna keep pitching like that?

1086
01:00:34,280 --> 01:00:35,280
My fingers hurt.

1087
01:00:35,320 --> 01:00:36,530
Stop pretending.

1088
01:00:37,320 --> 01:00:38,160
By the way,

1089
01:00:38,910 --> 01:00:41,080
why were you taking it out on me?

1090
01:00:47,080 --> 01:00:48,330
You like fried chicken?

1091
01:00:48,380 --> 01:00:49,750
Who doesn't?

1092
01:00:49,790 --> 01:00:51,670
I mean, is it your favorite?

1093
01:00:52,000 --> 01:00:55,340
Your mom left you fried chicken and cola, so it must be.

1094
01:00:55,380 --> 01:00:55,880
Yeah,

1095
01:00:56,510 --> 01:00:58,640
specifically the sweet and salty kind.

1096
01:00:58,800 --> 01:00:59,470
But why?

1097
01:01:00,890 --> 01:01:01,810
Let's go eat it.

1098
01:01:02,680 --> 01:01:03,180
Are you
kidding me?

1099
01:01:04,350 --> 01:01:05,890
You think I can go and eat it?

1100
01:01:11,150 --> 01:01:11,570
Well.

1101
01:01:13,610 --> 01:01:13,860
You are not

1102
01:01:14,900 --> 01:01:15,740
eating it?

1103
01:01:16,190 --> 01:01:17,320
I hate ketchup.

1104
01:01:17,360 --> 01:01:18,360
You can have my share too.

1105
01:01:18,410 --> 01:01:20,240
I don't like side dishes.

1106
01:01:20,320 --> 01:01:21,530
Wipe your drool.

1107
01:01:23,290 --> 01:01:24,290
Thank you.

1108
01:01:28,580 --> 01:01:29,330
What?

1109
01:01:31,130 --> 01:01:33,460
Always me wolfing it down.

1110
01:01:35,800 --> 01:01:36,460
Sorry.

1111
01:01:36,670 --> 01:01:37,590
It's okay.

1112
01:01:37,800 --> 01:01:39,430
Thank god you're slow.

1113
01:01:39,470 --> 01:01:39,970
Seriously!

1114
01:01:40,010 --> 01:01:43,010
If only you were slower then.

1115
01:01:43,050 --> 01:01:43,680
Forget it.

1116
01:01:44,260 --> 01:01:45,850
Anything you wanna do with me?

1117
01:01:45,890 --> 01:01:47,390
Yeah, I do.

1118
01:01:47,430 --> 01:01:50,310
You should have said so earlier!

1119
01:01:50,350 --> 01:01:51,350
We're out of time,

1120
01:01:51,560 --> 01:01:52,360
and you choose now?

1121
01:01:52,400 --> 01:01:54,570
You were sulking and wouldn't talk.

1122
01:01:54,610 --> 01:01:55,570
When was I
like that?

1123
01:01:57,900 --> 01:01:59,360
Then what do you want to do?

1124
01:02:00,160 --> 01:02:01,070
There's a place.

1125
01:02:02,120 --> 01:02:03,870
I want to go there with you.

1126
01:02:07,450 --> 01:02:08,120
Are we almost there?

1127
01:02:09,000 --> 01:02:10,330
Still far.

1128
01:02:10,370 --> 01:02:12,330
We're not taking the less gentle path, are we?

1129
01:02:12,830 --> 01:02:14,290
With the time we have left?

1130
01:02:15,670 --> 01:02:16,710
Hold on tight.

1131
01:02:16,760 --> 01:02:17,590
I'm speeding up.

1132
01:02:34,020 --> 01:02:34,400
Hey!

1133
01:02:34,440 --> 01:02:36,070
Stop here.

1134
01:02:40,240 --> 01:02:40,860
Why here?
Let's go.

1135
01:02:41,860 --> 01:02:42,950
Finish what we started.

1136
01:02:45,530 --> 01:02:46,240
Finish what?

1137
01:02:46,410 --> 01:02:48,450
The game we didn't finish in middle school.

1138
01:02:48,500 --> 01:02:50,290
If I had gotten a hit then,

1139
01:02:50,330 --> 01:02:52,000
my team would have made the finals,

1140
01:02:52,210 --> 01:02:52,670
right?

1141
01:02:53,420 --> 01:02:54,000
Let's go.

1142
01:03:07,390 --> 01:03:08,930
Are you just going to stand there?

1143
01:03:09,470 --> 01:03:12,520
Open the gate or something.

1144
01:03:12,560 --> 01:03:13,270
I can't.

1145
01:03:14,270 --> 01:03:15,560
I can't do anything.

1146
01:03:15,610 --> 01:03:16,820
Why not?

1147
01:03:16,900 --> 01:03:19,570
You can catch, you can hit, you can do everything.

1148
01:03:19,820 --> 01:03:21,280
Only with you.

1149
01:03:21,610 --> 01:03:22,110
Alright.

1150
01:03:24,070 --> 01:03:26,530
There must be a way in.

1151
01:03:29,080 --> 01:03:29,580
Hey!

1152
01:03:30,160 --> 01:03:31,120
Wait for me here.

1153
01:03:44,430 --> 01:03:45,260
He's late.

1154
01:04:21,590 --> 01:04:21,960
Hey,

1155
01:04:22,630 --> 01:04:23,590
how did you get in?

1156
01:04:23,630 --> 01:04:25,380
Used the same magic as you.

1157
01:04:25,570 --> 01:04:26,140
Nice one.
What?

1158
01:04:27,010 --> 01:04:27,640
Are you mocking me?
No.

1159
01:04:28,970 --> 01:04:30,060
Show me what you've got again.

1160
01:04:30,640 --> 01:04:31,100
What?

1161
01:04:31,140 --> 01:04:32,810
That game we didn't finish.

1162
01:04:32,850 --> 01:04:33,270
Alright.

1163
01:04:33,310 --> 01:04:34,640
Come on.

1164
01:04:34,680 --> 01:04:36,900
As a player, I always doubted

1165
01:04:37,190 --> 01:04:38,150
if I really had the talent.
So

1166
01:04:38,730 --> 01:04:40,110
this is your unfinished business.

1167
01:04:40,150 --> 01:04:41,190
Yes, it is.

1168
01:04:41,610 --> 01:04:42,230
But what could I do?

1169
01:04:42,820 --> 01:04:43,530
It was my dream.

1170
01:04:44,820 --> 01:04:45,530
So
I see.

1171
01:04:46,570 --> 01:04:47,490
You just can't help it.

1172
01:04:47,950 --> 01:04:49,370
So, for me to rest in peace,

1173
01:04:49,410 --> 01:04:51,620
show me I wasn't that good.

1174
01:04:51,950 --> 01:04:53,200
I want you to prove it.

1175
01:04:53,500 --> 01:04:53,950
Alright.

1176
01:04:54,370 --> 01:04:56,870
I'll crush this dream of yours.

1177
01:04:57,120 --> 01:04:58,630
Don't go easy on me out of pity.

1178
01:04:58,790 --> 01:04:59,290
Of course not.

1179
01:04:59,330 --> 01:05:02,340
I can't let my friend wander the earth as a ghost.

1180
01:05:02,550 --> 01:05:03,380
Ghost?

1181
01:05:03,760 --> 01:05:06,510
But I'll give it my all.

1182
01:05:06,550 --> 01:05:07,090
Okay,

1183
01:05:07,130 --> 01:05:08,340
bring it on.

1184
01:05:08,390 --> 01:05:09,180
Ready?
Yeah!

1185
01:05:13,470 --> 01:05:14,470
Top of the 9th, two outs.

1186
01:05:14,720 --> 01:05:15,850
Runners on 1st and 2nd.

1187
01:05:16,430 --> 01:05:18,730
The batter is Kwon Tae-seop.

1188
01:05:30,740 --> 01:05:32,740
One hit ties the game at 4-4.

1189
01:05:32,910 --> 01:05:34,870
It feels like we're back here again.

1190
01:05:34,910 --> 01:05:35,830
Focus.

1191
01:05:40,500 --> 01:05:41,630
I'll pitch without regrets.

1192
01:05:45,550 --> 01:05:46,130
Play ball!

1193
01:05:57,020 --> 01:05:57,770
Ball!

1194
01:05:59,350 --> 01:06:00,350
Hey, Lee Woo-jin!

1195
01:06:00,520 --> 01:06:01,690
Pull yourself together!

1196
01:06:01,730 --> 01:06:02,610
Not again.

1197
01:06:02,900 --> 01:06:05,070
Just slipped.

1198
01:06:05,110 --> 01:06:06,780
You better give it your all.

1199
01:06:06,820 --> 01:06:07,530
Don't worry.

1200
01:06:08,490 --> 01:06:10,070
I'm only thinking about this.

1201
01:06:15,370 --> 01:06:16,200
Here it comes.

1202
01:06:22,880 --> 01:06:23,460
Here it comes.

1203
01:06:29,300 --> 01:06:30,510
One strike, one ball.

1204
01:06:31,180 --> 01:06:31,590
Hey,

1205
01:06:32,010 --> 01:06:33,970
the ball looks even faster from here.

1206
01:06:40,440 --> 01:06:41,900
One strike, two balls.

1207
01:06:42,440 --> 01:06:43,230
That's a really good pitch.

1208
01:06:50,070 --> 01:06:50,450
What?

1209
01:06:51,240 --> 01:06:51,700
Damn it!
Foul ball!

1210
01:06:58,830 --> 01:07:00,660
Why do I keep fouling it off?

1211
01:07:04,880 --> 01:07:06,630
Another foul ball.

1212
01:07:23,770 --> 01:07:25,100
Two strikes, three balls.

1213
01:07:25,150 --> 01:07:25,900
Alright.

1214
01:07:26,480 --> 01:07:28,020
Full count.

1215
01:07:41,040 --> 01:07:41,660
What?

1216
01:07:41,910 --> 01:07:43,000
Strikeout?

1217
01:07:43,040 --> 01:07:43,960
Not exactly.

1218
01:07:44,000 --> 01:07:45,580
It means everything comes down to this pitch.

1219
01:08:05,400 --> 01:08:05,900
No way.

1220
01:08:06,270 --> 01:08:07,520
Are you going to hit a home run?

1221
01:08:09,610 --> 01:08:10,860
Yeah, a home run.

1222
01:08:11,820 --> 01:08:13,440
That would turn things around, you know?

1223
01:08:13,950 --> 01:08:15,820
Fine, whatever you say.

1224
01:08:18,530 --> 01:08:19,130
Here it comes.

1225
01:08:48,230 --> 01:08:49,020
Damn it!

1226
01:08:50,610 --> 01:08:51,690
Three outs.

1227
01:08:51,730 --> 01:08:53,030
Game over.

1228
01:08:59,660 --> 01:09:01,740
My bat got stung,

1229
01:09:01,950 --> 01:09:04,040
completely different from

1230
01:09:04,080 --> 01:09:05,540
what I imagined.

1231
01:09:05,580 --> 01:09:07,750
I analyzed your pitching for a year.

1232
01:09:07,790 --> 01:09:09,960
The real level is completely different,

1233
01:09:10,000 --> 01:09:11,460
ten times more powerful.

1234
01:09:11,500 --> 01:09:12,170
Probably.

1235
01:09:12,210 --> 01:09:14,010
Chapter one is full of old data now.

1236
01:09:14,420 --> 01:09:15,170
You read it!

1237
01:09:15,380 --> 01:09:16,260
Training with you

1238
01:09:16,970 --> 01:09:18,130
made me ten times stronger

1239
01:09:19,550 --> 01:09:21,100
than I was back then.

1240
01:09:32,520 --> 01:09:33,820
Today's a big day.

1241
01:09:33,860 --> 01:09:34,610
We have the finals.
Jeong-ho.

1242
01:09:35,490 --> 01:09:37,240
Don't go easy on your idol.

1243
01:09:37,740 --> 01:09:38,110
Okay.

1244
01:09:38,740 --> 01:09:39,990
I'll play without regrets.

1245
01:09:43,830 --> 01:09:44,580
Thanks.

1246
01:09:45,700 --> 01:09:47,080
I have no regrets.

1247
01:09:47,290 --> 01:09:49,000
Me neither.

1248
01:09:50,120 --> 01:09:52,340
Nothing can stop you from getting in top form now.

1249
01:09:52,380 --> 01:09:52,840
Why?

1250
01:09:53,130 --> 01:09:54,880
We made new memories today.

1251
01:10:01,910 --> 01:10:02,620
What?

1252
01:10:02,990 --> 01:10:04,220
You're quiet.

1253
01:10:04,260 --> 01:10:04,890
Did you

1254
01:10:05,390 --> 01:10:07,730
arrange this game for me?

1255
01:10:07,960 --> 01:10:08,340
Ah.

1256
01:10:08,850 --> 01:10:10,270
Yes and no.

1257
01:10:15,070 --> 01:10:15,940
Even until the end,

1258
01:10:16,480 --> 01:10:17,650
you only care about me.

1259
01:10:20,200 --> 01:10:21,990
I just want to do what I could too.

1260
01:10:22,410 --> 01:10:23,570
I don't want to have any regrets.

1261
01:10:24,530 --> 01:10:26,200
I wanna leave without regrets.

1262
01:10:26,240 --> 01:10:28,790
Why care about me so much until the very end?

1263
01:10:29,120 --> 01:10:30,960
I'm not as fragile as you thought.

1264
01:10:31,120 --> 01:10:31,620
I know.

1265
01:10:32,500 --> 01:10:33,920
I know you're strong.

1266
01:10:35,000 --> 01:10:35,960
Stronger than anyone.
Then why?

1267
01:10:37,420 --> 01:10:38,760
Don't worry about me anymore.

1268
01:10:38,800 --> 01:10:39,300
I won't.

1269
01:10:41,680 --> 01:10:42,890
Even if I wanted to, I can't.

1270
01:10:47,060 --> 01:10:47,560
No!

1271
01:10:54,480 --> 01:10:55,820
I have to go.

1272
01:10:55,980 --> 01:10:56,440
What?

1273
01:10:56,900 --> 01:10:57,780
Just like that?

1274
01:10:59,610 --> 01:11:01,490
You can't just leave.

1275
01:11:03,950 --> 01:11:04,490
Woo-jin.

1276
01:11:10,290 --> 01:11:11,540
I have one request.

1277
01:11:12,370 --> 01:11:12,870
You must

1278
01:11:13,250 --> 01:11:14,790
win the High School MVP.

1279
01:11:17,090 --> 01:11:18,000
That was

1280
01:11:18,590 --> 01:11:20,760
my goal. With you.

1281
01:11:20,800 --> 01:11:22,430
As long as you don't forget me,

1282
01:11:22,840 --> 01:11:24,090
I'll always be with you.

1283
01:11:24,140 --> 01:11:25,760
How could I ever forget you?

1284
01:11:34,900 --> 01:11:35,520
Tae-hui,

1285
01:11:37,570 --> 01:11:39,190
keep watching me, okay?

1286
01:11:39,360 --> 01:11:40,110
I will.

1287
01:11:46,780 --> 01:11:47,990
Goodbye, my friend.

1288
01:11:51,410 --> 01:11:52,370
Goodbye, Tae-hui.

1289
01:12:04,510 --> 01:12:05,800
Goodbye.

1290
01:12:29,120 --> 01:12:30,160
A lucky charm.

1291
01:12:33,750 --> 01:12:36,040
2025 Haegi Cup National High School Baseball Tournament,

1292
01:12:36,080 --> 01:12:37,960
